g credit based on each school''s academic requirements.\r\n\r\nTo see information about PLA at the University of Maine at Augusta: <a target="_blank" href="http://www.uma.edu/testingassessment.html">Click here</a>.\r\n\r\nTo see information about PLA at the University of Southern Maine: <a target="_blank" href="http://www.usm.maine.edu/pla">CLick here</a>.\r\n\r\n<a target="_blank" href="http://www.cael.org/home">The Center for Adult &amp; Experiential Learning (CAEL)</a> is a great resource to learn about PLA.[/accordion][accordion title="Jobs in Maine"]<a target="_blank" href="http://www.maine.gov/labor/labor_stats/jobs_in_demand.shtml#associates">Jobs you can do in Maine with an associate’s degree</a>.\r\n<a target="_blank" href="http://www.maine.gov/labor/labor_stats/jobs_in_demand.shtml#bachelors">Jobs you could do in Maine with a bachelor’s degree</a>.[/accordion]</li><li><h1><span>3)</span>Pay for College</h2>[accordion title="Finance Authority of Maine"]<a target="_blank" href="http://www.famemaine.com/Education_Home.aspx">The Finance Authority of Maine</a> provides free information on planning and paying for college, career preparation and financial education, including responsible borrowing. \r\n\r\nFAME has tools and information specifically to help adult students plan for and start college. Find everything here from choosing a career or college, to balancing school with work and family, to applying to college and paying for school, and much more: To access the FAME tools, <a target="_blank" href="http://www.famemaine.com/files/Pages/education/students_and_families/Non-Traditional_Students.aspx">CLick here</a>.[/accordion]</li><li><h1><span>4)</span>FAQ</h1>[accordion title="Should I take an online program?"]Many of the programs that work best for adult students who have jobs, families and other obligations are online programs. This option may or may not work for you. Some of the <a target="_blank" href="http://www.maineadulted.org/">Maine Adult Education</a> programs offer introductory courses in online learning.\r\n\r\nThere are other assessments and guides you can take a look at to assess whether you’re a good candidate for online classes &amp; programs. For example, the <a target="_blank" href="http://online.sjcme.edu/pdf/learningonlineguide.pdf">Saint Joseph’s College of Maine online guide</a>[/accordion]</li></ul>', 'Start College', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '20-revision-11', '', '', '2012-06-12 17:57:02', '2012-06-12 17:57:02', '', 20, 'http://www.nextstepmaine.org/20-revision-11/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
