e college credit for what you’ve learned through work. This can save you time and money if you’re planning to get a college degree by eliminating the number of classes you may need to take. Colleges and universities in Maine have different methods of awarding credit based on each school''s academic requirements.\r\nView information about PLA at the <a href="http://www.uma.edu/testingassessment.html" target="_blank">University of Maine at Augusta</a> or information about PLA at the <a href="http://www.usm.maine.edu/pla" target="_blank">University of Southern Maine</a>.\r\nThe <a href="http://www.cael.org/home" target="_blank">Center for Adult &amp; Experiential Learning (CAEL)</a> is also a great resource to learn about PLA[/accordion][accordion title="Jobs in Maine"]See the list of <a href="http://www.maine.gov/labor/labor_stats/jobs_in_demand.shtml" target="_blank">jobs that are growing in Maine</a> that require a high school diploma or GED.[/accordion]</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Get a GED', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '18-revision-21', '', '', '2012-06-29 17:06:35', '2012-06-29 17:06:35', '', 18, 'http://www.nextstepmaine.org/18-revision-21/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
