(4866, 2, '2012-08-17 17:14:57', '2012-08-17 17:14:57', '<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h1 class="inline moreleading">Starting college can be daunting and exciting all at once.</h1>\r\n<h2 class="inline moreleading">Click through the resources and links below to find more information about how to get started. Or choose from the menu below to explore specific programs offered in Maine.</h2>\r\nThere are lots of reasons that your next step should be to start college: to encourage your kids to go to college, change careers or earn a bigger paycheck, or simply to feel the sense of accomplishment that comes with that diploma.\r\n\r\nMore and more jobs in the future will require a college degree of some kind. Workers who have college degrees also earn more over their lifetimes than those who don’t. So, college may be a smart next step for you.\r\n\r\nThe question is: where do you start? Good news: there are a lot of resources available to you in Maine. On this site, you can explore jobs that require a college degree and are growing in Maine. You can browse or search for programs and institutions that might be of interest to you. You can find help figuring out how to pay for college, and much more.\r\n\r\nBrowse 2 or 4 year degree programs, certificates or advanced degrees available in Maine.\r\n<ul class="program-types">\r\n<li><a title="Certificates in Maine" href="http://www.nextstepmaine.org/programs/certificate">Certificates</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title="Associate Degrees in Maine" href="http://www.nextstepmaine.org/programs/associate">Associates Degrees</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title="Bachelor Degrees in Maine" href="http://www.nextstepmaine.org/programs/bachelor">Bachelors Degrees</a></li>\r\n	<li class="last"><a title="Masters Degrees in Maine" href="http://www.nextstepmaine.org/programs/master">Advanced Degrees</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3>LINKS &amp; RESOURCES</h3>\r\n[accordion title="Get Help from Your Employer"]If you have a job, your first step should be to find out what supports your employer may offer to further your education and training. Many employers offer tuition assistance, flexible scheduling or on-site training to help increase employees’ skills &amp; knowledge. If your employer is part of the Maine Employers’ Initiative, you are entitled to tuition discounts from several institutions in Maine: If your employer is on <a href="http://www.mdf.org/mei_employers.php" target="_blank">this list</a>, ask them about it![/accordion][accordion title="The College Transitions Program"]The College Transitions Program is a great first step. Adult Education can help you explore your college options, figure out if you’re ready – and if you’re not ready, they’ll help you get ready. The Maine College Transitions Program (offered through Adult Education programs around the state)<strong> </strong>is designed to help adult students transition into college. They will provide support with applications and financial aid, college prep classes, college and career planning, placement testing, and individual advising. For a more complete description of the program: <a href="http://www.maine.gov/education/aded/dev/transitions/mctp%20description%20revised%202010.doc" target="_blank">Click here</a>. For the location of a College''s Transitions program: <a href="http://www.maine.gov/education/aded/dev/transitions/MCT.Contact._info.pdf" target="_blank">Click here</a>.[/accordion][accordion title="College Entrance Examination Preparation"]<a href="http://www.maine.gov/msl/commons/learnexp/index.shtml" target="_blank">LearningExpress Library</a> is offered by the Maine State Library and features over 770 practice tests, tutorials, and eBooks related to job search and workplace skills improvement, career certification and licensing exam preparation, college entrance and graduate school admissions exam preparation, GED exam preparation, and basic skills improvement in reading, writing, and math, for all ages.\r\n\r\nYou will get immediate scoring, complete answer explanations, and an individualized analysis of your results. In addition, you will find interactive popular software tutorials/courses that are video-based and allow you to learn at your own pace.[/accordion][accordion title="Get College Credit for Work Experience"]Prior Learning Assessment or PLA is a way that you can receive college credit for what you’ve learned through work. This can save you time and money if you’re planning to get a college degree by eliminating the number of classes you may need to take. Colleges and universities in Maine have different methods of awarding credit based on each school''s academic requirements.\r\n\r\nTo see information about PLA at the University of Maine at Augusta: <a href="http://www.uma.edu/testingassessment.html" target="_blank">Click here</a>.\r\n\r\nTo see information about PLA at the University of Southern Maine: <a href="http://www.usm.maine.edu/pla" target="_blank">CLick here</a>.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.cael.org/home" target="_blank">The Center for Adult &amp; Experiential Learning (CAEL)</a> is a great resource to learn about PLA.[/accordion][accordion title="Jobs in Maine"]<a title="High-Growth jobs in Maine with only an Associates Degree" href="http://www.nextstepmaine.org/jobs/associate/">Jobs you can do in Maine with an associate’s degree</a>.\r\n<a title="High-Growth Jobs in Maine with only a Bachelor''s Degree" href="http://www.nextstepmaine.org/jobs/bachelor/" target="_blank">Jobs you could do in Maine with a bachelor’s degree</a>.[/accordion]</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3>Pay for College</h3>\r\n[accordion title="Finance Authority of Maine"]<a href="http://www.famemaine.com/Education_Home.aspx" target="_blank">The Finance Authority of Maine</a> provides free information on planning and paying for college, career preparation and financial education, including responsible borrowing.\r\n\r\nFAME has tools and information specifically to help adult students plan for and start college. Find everything here from choosing a career or college, to balancing school with work and family, to applying to college and paying for school, and much more: To access the FAME tools, <a href="http://www.famemaine.com/files/Pages/education/students_and_families/Non-Traditional_Students.aspx" target="_blank">CLick here</a>.[/accordion]</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Start College', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '20-revision-30', '', '', '2012-08-17 17:14:57', '2012-08-17 17:14:57', '', 20, 'http://www.nextstepmaine.org/20-revision-30/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
