(6030, 1, '2012-10-01 15:44:46', '2012-10-01 15:44:46', '<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h1 class="inline moreleading">Taking The GED<sup>®</sup> Test is an important step.</h1>\r\n<h2 class="inline moreleading">Use the links below to find programs to prepare, testing locations, and much more.</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\nIf your next step involves graduating from high school or taking the GED<sup>&reg;</sup> test (high school equivalency degree test), you’re in luck. There are 84 testing sites across the state, offered through Adult and Community Education programs. These programs offer orientation classes and pre-testing as well.\r\n\r\nView Information about <a href="http://www.maine.gov/education/aded/dev/hsc.htm" target="_blank">GED<sup>&reg;</sup> &amp; high school diploma programs</a> through Maine Adult Education, along with the list of <a href="http://www.maine.gov/education/aded/dev/data/GED2010.pdf" target="_blank">locations that offer GED<sup>&reg;</sup> testing programs</a> in Maine. Another valuable resource to prospective test takers can be found at the <a title="GED Test Services website" href="http://www.gedtestingservice.com/testers/test-taker-home" target="_blank">GED<sup>&reg;</sup> Testing Service website</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3>LINKS &amp; RESOURCES</h3>\r\n[accordion title="Take a practice test"]<a href="http://www.maine.gov/msl/commons/learnexp/index.shtml" target="_blank">The Maine State Library</a> offers a variety of study aids and practice tests, including GED. Also refer to the <a href="http://www.maineadulted.org/" target="_blank">Maine Adult Education website</a> to see what’s available in your area.[/accordion][accordion title="Is Your Next Step College?"]Adult Education can help you explore college options as well. <a href="http://www.maine.gov/education/aded/dev/transitions.htm" target="_blank">The College Transitions Program</a>(offered through Adult Education programs around the state)helps adult students transition into college. Get support with applications and financial aid, college prep classes, college and career planning, placement testing, and individual advising.\r\n\r\nAdults in Maine who want to go to community college, as well as some of the other public Universities, may need to take the placement test Accuplacer. The ACCUPLACER® is a set of exams that quickly and accurately assess reading, writing, math, and computer skills. This process is designed to evaluate readiness for college level work.   Individual colleges and universities administer the tests, so just ask if it’s a requirement that applies to you and if so, when, where and how you can take the test.  If you’re nervous about these placement tests, talk with your local adult education office or College Transitions counselor.  Maine''s Career and Technical Education centers, community colleges and state universities use the ACCUPLACER® extensively to track achievement and to determine course placements.  For more information go to:  <a title="Maine DOE Accuplacer" href="http://www.maine.gov/education/mhsa/accuplacer.html" target="_blank">Maine DOE Accuplacer Page</a>.[/accordion][accordion title="Get College Credit for Work Experience"]\r\n\r\nPrior Learning Assessment or PLA is a way that you can receive college credit for what you’ve learned through work. This can save you time and money if you’re planning to get a college degree by eliminating the number of classes you may need to take. Colleges and universities in Maine have different methods of awarding credit based on each school''s academic requirements.\r\n\r\nTo see information about PLA at the University of Maine at Augusta: <a href="http://www.uma.edu/testingassessment.html" target="_blank">Click here</a>.\r\n\r\nTo see information about PLA at the University of Southern Maine: <a href="http://www.usm.maine.edu/pla" target="_blank">Click here</a>.\r\n\r\nTo see information about PLA at Saint Joseph’s College of Maine: <a href="http://online.sjcme.edu/continuing-education-units-opportunities.php" target="_blank">Click here</a>.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.cael.org/home" target="_blank">The Center for Adult &amp; Experiential Learning (CAEL)</a> is a great resource to learn about PLA.\r\n\r\n[/accordion][accordion title="Jobs in Maine"]See the list of <a title="High-Growth Jobs in Maine" href="http://www.nextstepmaine.org/jobs/">jobs that are growing in Maine</a> that require a high school diploma or GED.[/accordion]</li>\r\n</ul>', 'GED<sup>&reg;</sup> testing', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '18-revision-50', '', '', '2012-10-01 15:44:46', '2012-10-01 15:44:46', '', 18, 'http://www.nextstepmaine.org/18-revision-50/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(6031, 1, '2012-09-13 20:31:25', '2012-09-13 20:31:25', '<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h1 class="inline moreleading">Changing your Career.</h1><h2 class="inline moreleading"> Use the resources and links below to explore jobs available in Maine, or use the menu buttons below to explore specific programs that may qualify you for a new career.</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\nThe majority of us have multiple careers during our lifetimes.  If you’re considering making a change, we’ve compiled some resources to help.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.mainecareercenter.com/employment/training-adults/index.shtml" target="_blank">Maine’s Career Centers</a> are a great place to start assessing what your next step might be. They can provide information about how to decide what career is right for you, and how to get the right training to be qualified. To see the full list of career center locations <a href="http://www.mainecareercenter.com/locations/index.shtml" target="_blank">Click here</a>\r\n\r\n<a title="High-Growth Jobs in Maine" href="http://www.nextstepmaine.org/jobs/">Jobs in demand in Maine</a> provides a list of job fields around Maine that are projected to be growing and in demand in the state.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.mainecareercenter.com/employment/search/index.shtml" target="_blank">The Maine Job Bank</a> also has a list of jobs available now around the state of Maine.\r\n\r\nBrowse certificate programs, associate programs, bachelor programs, or master programs available in Maine.\r\n<ul class="program-types">\r\n	<li><a title="Certificate Programs in Maine" href="http://www.nextstepmaine.org/programs/certificate">Certificate Programs</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title="Associate Programs in Maine" href="http://www.nextstepmaine.org/programs/associate">Associates Programs</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title="Bachelor Programs in Maine" href="http://www.nextstepmaine.org/programs/bachelor">Bachelors Programs</a></li>\r\n	<li class="last"><a title="Masters Programs in Maine" href="http://www.nextstepmaine.org/programs/master">Advanced Programs</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3>Links and Resources</h3>\r\n[accordion title="Resources to Explore New Careers"]<a href="http://www.maine.gov/msl/commons/learnexp/index.shtml" target="_blank">LearningExpress Library</a> is offered by the Maine State Library and features over 770 practice tests, tutorials, and eBooks related to job search and workplace skills improvement, career certification and licensing exam preparation, college entrance and graduate school admissions exam preparation, GED exam preparation, and basic skills improvement in reading, writing, and math, for all ages.\r\n\r\nYou will get immediate scoring, complete answer explanations, and an individualized analysis of your results.  In addition, you will find interactive popular software tutorials/courses that are video-based and allow you to learn at your own pace.[/accordion]</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Change My Career', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '27-revision-31', '', '', '2012-09-13 20:31:25', '2012-09-13 20:31:25', '', 27, 'http://www.nextstepmaine.org/27-revision-31/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(6033, 1, '2012-09-12 20:34:23', '2012-09-12 20:34:23', 'The following programs are offered at institutions around the state of Maine. Use the filter and sort tools below to find the programs you''re interested in learning about. This site does not currently list programs at the individual community colleges. To see programs offered at these schools, please find them in the list of institutions and link directly to the program lists from there.', 'Maine Educational Programs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2062-revision-5', '', '', '2012-09-12 20:34:23', '2012-09-12 20:34:23', '', 2062, 'http://www.nextstepmaine.org/2062-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(6036, 1, '2012-11-16 14:39:47', '2012-11-16 14:39:47', '<ul>\n	<li>Virtually every college or university will have counselors and people to help you along the way. The best thing to do is start with people in the admissions office, and they will help you weigh your options as well as connect you with college and career counselors moving forward. (You can find admissions office contact information on this site for each institution listed here.)</li>\n	<li>Regarding online programs: Every online program at each college or university is different and will have varying degrees of interaction and guidance. You should always contact the admissions office and find out how the program functions, what the expectations are, how much time you may need to set aside for work at home. Ask to speak to a faculty member or advisor if you don’t get all of the details you need from the admissions office.</li>\n</ul>', 'What if I need help – are there real people to talk to or interact with? What about with online colleges and universities?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2406-autosave', '', '', '2012-11-16 14:39:47', '2012-11-16 14:39:47', '', 2406, 'http://www.nextstepmaine.org/2406-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(6829, 1, '2013-04-15 13:40:13', '2013-04-15 13:40:13', 'At Beal College, our mission is to partner with our students as they pursue their academic journeys. We have a small campus with small classes and we offer personalized attention to our students. Plus, Beal students come from all backgrounds, so no matter your age or experience, you’ll feel comfortable here!\nIf you’re dreaming of a new career or hoping to advance your current career, Beal can help. We offer affordable hands-on training for the careers of today and beyond – and financial aid is available to those who qualify. Beal offers a convenient class schedule with 6 start dates during the year. Full-time students only take 2 courses per term.', 'Beal College', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beal-college', '', '', '2013-04-15 13:40:13', '2013-04-15 13:40:13', '', 0, 'http://www.nextstepmaine.org/institution/beal-college/', 0, 'nsm_institution', '', 0),
(6850, 1, '2013-04-15 13:53:11', '2013-04-15 13:53:11', 'The Accounting program is designed to give the student an in-depth knowledge of accounting principles and their application in today’s business environment. Specialized courses including Federal Taxes, Managerial Accounting and Computerized Accounting are included to provide the student with a wider range of business knowledge.', 'Accounting', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'accounting', '', '', '2013-04-15 13:53:11', '2013-04-15 13:53:11', '', 0, 'http://www.nextstepmaine.org/program/accounting/', 0, 'nsm_program', '', 0),
