(7277, 1, '2013-04-15 14:01:21', '2013-04-15 14:01:21', 'Franco American Studies is an interdisciplinary program that explores the French cultures of the United States and Canada, emphasizing the people of Franco American heritage in Maine and the Northeast region. It studies Franco American culture within the broader context of American ethnic communities and other French-speaking people worldwide. The curriculum is designed to teach the Franco American past and present: topics of study include problems of identity, the politics of language, literature, historical struggles, women’s issues and experience, economic structures, and the role of family.', 'Franco American Studies', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'franco-american-studies', '', '', '2013-04-15 14:01:21', '2013-04-15 14:01:21', '', 0, 'http://www.nextstepmaine.org/program/franco-american-studies/', 0, 'nsm_program', '', 0),
